The User's function (of any name to choose)
gives the real value of the FINAL ELEVATION Z
of the INITIAL POINT of coordinates x,y,z. 

This function must have the 4 parameters  no_slice x y z
in this order and programmed with respect to the LU language grammar.
(cf documentation of menu debut)

For the execution, the parameters no_slice x y z will be initialized.
They may be used or not to compute the ELEVATION value.
            
EXAMPLE:
deffunc ELEVATION( no_slice , x , y , z ) ; 
   if    (no_slice>2)
   then  ELEVATION = z + 0.3;
   else  ELEVATION = z * 1.2;
   endif;  
endfunc; 
